Web API interface description

Security Mechanism
  • The WEB API interface can only be used after login, and the resource service interface used for login is auth;
  • The auth interface uses two-step login authentication, and a SessionID will be returned after successful login;
  • For each API request, the SessionID needs to be added to the Cookie field of the HTTP request header;
  • If the API request involves password, personal or other sensitive information, the original information must be encrypted using the AES encryption algorithm, and the key is the SessionID of the currently logged-in session;
  • When obtaining the encrypted field of the ID card number, the user needs to first issue the AES key to the device through the special operation interface.
error handling

There are two types of error handling:

  1. A protocol error is caused by an incorrect format of the protocol message. When the HTTP header is wrong, or illegal data is received, or a socket timeout is encountered, the receiver will receive a protocol error. In order to indicate and explain protocol errors, the HTTP protocol defines a set of standard status codes [such as 1xx, 2xx, 3xx, 4xx, 5xx]. For details, please refer to Common HTTP Status Codes;
HTTP status codes describe
200 OK The server successfully returns the data requested by the user
201 Created User created data successfully
202 Accepted Indicates that a request has entered the background queue (asynchronous task)
204 No Content User deleted data successfully
400 Bad Request There is an error in the request data from the user
401 Unauthorized Indicates that the user does not have permission (token, username, wrong password)
403 Forbidden Indicates that the user is authorized (as opposed to a 401 error), but access is forbidden
404 Not Found Indicates that the resource requested by the user does not exist
405 Method Not Allowed The request method specified in the request line cannot be used to request the corresponding resource
500 Internal Server Error The server encountered an unexpected condition and could not complete the request
503 Service Unavailable Server resources temporarily unavailable
  1. Errors returned by resource operations, such as adding or deleting face photos, querying access records due to operating device resources, usually return an HTTP status code greater than 400, and the response body returns an error data described in json format. The general format is as follows :
{
errors：[
    {
        "status": 503,
        "source": { "pointer": "/devices/status" },
        "title": "Service Unavailable",
        "detail": "worker is busy",
        "error_code": -1
    }
]
}
describe
status HTTP status codes
title HTTP Status Description
source Resource name, json pointer type
detail For the description of the error message, please refer to each interface document for details.
error_code Error status code, see each interface documentation for details
ext_param Error expansion field, tentatively used to return the name of the person who has been put into the warehouse (W5K model is not supported for the time being)
General Error Code Table

Below is a table of common error codes covering most possible errors, including:

  • {parameter_name} and {resource_name} correspond to Field Name and Resource Type respectively in the actual returned response
  • The status column is the HTTP status code of the response;
  • title is listed as HTTP status description or specific error;
  • The information in the detail column may differ slightly from the actual response returned, usually to indicate a more specific error message.

usage restrictions

The WEB API interface can use all functions only when the device is in local mode; the functions are limited in cloud mode and server mode, such as only personnel, personnel groups and access control plan parameters can be obtained, and cannot be added or modified.

HTTP response
  1. The body of the response is directly the data, do not overpack;
  2. The data format after each HTTP method is successfully processed:
response format
GET single object, collection
POST Add a successful object
PUT object updated successfully
DELETE null
  1. The convention of json format The
    time format adopts the ISO 8601 standard, such as "2020-01-01T18:25:43[.322]+08:00", [.322][ represents an option, which is milliseconds; the
    picture adopts the urldata format, that is The base64 encoded data is added with the header of "data:image/jpeg;base64,".
  2. The json data format of complex query paging response is specified as follows:
{
"paging":{"limit":10,"offset":0,"total":729},
"data":[ {},{},{}...]
}
  1. The links attribute indicates that there are associated resources, rel indicates the relationship between this API and the current resource, and href indicates the path of the API;
Asynchronous API

HTTP-based access interfaces are all synchronous, but when users call certain resources, sometimes the resources cannot respond immediately or are performing very time-consuming operations, such as upgrades, photo storage, etc., which need to be processed asynchronously;
By designing the status and return data of HTTP, the effect of asynchronous request can be achieved. The steps are as follows:

  1. The user requests an asynchronous operation, such as uploading a file to the upgrade interface;
  2. The upgrade interface receives the upgrade file data, and after checking it, returns the HTTP 202 Accepted status code, and gives the interface for obtaining the upgrade status in the json return value:
HTTP/1.1 202 Accepted
{
  "href": "/api/devices/firmware/status",
  "method": "get"
}
  1. After receiving the 202 status code, the user parses the href field of json to obtain the url of the upgrade status, and checks the upgrade status at regular intervals, such as 1 second;
  2. When the upgrade status returned in the json return value for obtaining the upgrade status is finished, the upgrade is complete, otherwise the corresponding upgrade error code will be given.

device login

Basic Information

Path: /api/auth/login

Method: POST

Interface description:

The password field algorithm in the request: hash(pwd, salt, challenge), the hash adopts the SHA2-256 algorithm, pwd is the actual password, and salt and challenge are the corresponding values ​​returned by the authentication challenge interface; if the
login fails 5 times, it will be locked User IP address, time 30 minutes;
after successful login, if the user does not perform api operations within 5 minutes, the login will be forcibly logged out.

Login example, the plaintext login password is admin123:

ciphertext is only required for W5K models. Different versions have different encryption types. The calculation method for version 1.1.9 is:

base64(AES(admin123))，密钥为session_id，加密模式CBC/PKCS7Padding，偏移量为0000000000000000

The calculation method for version 1.2.0 and later is:

base64(AES(admin123))，密钥为session_id，加密模式ECB/PKCS7Padding

The returned challenge json data:

{
    "session_id": "bfe6d6839bf228d4417d0ce4806b47ad",
    "challenge": "lmnnq3w0s10d3ig6x2h10xnk9x2esg2",
    "salt": "6923qx5z9yv3d2k5zx915apze209iyp7rhdjf6l25t3t47om9xqd6353vjy3831",
    "ciphertext": "lS0tyjt+bfoKchdphTMF1Q=="
}

Calculate the password field:

sha256(admin1236923qx5z9yv3d2k5zx915apze209iyp7rhdjf6l25t3t47om9xqd6353vjy3831lmnnq3w0s10d3ig6x2h10xnk9x2esg2)=c163a49044a9b7db99fd8171516c76f21deea3b970cc550d43503c1e4c663e8a

The login json data sent:

{
    "session_id": "bfe6d6839bf228d4417d0ce4806b47ad",
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "c163a49044a9b7db99fd8171516c76f21deea3b970cc550d43503c1e4c663e8a"
}

The ciphertext extension field is only used by W5K temporarily. The encryption method is AES (password, SessionID), and the SessionID is the session id of the local login.

Device Activation Authentication Challenge

Basic Information

Path: /api/auth/activation

Method: POST

Interface description:

This interface does not require Session authentication; the
public key needs to be saved by the client, and the entire activation process requires the public key to decode!

Request public_key generation process Javascript example, using cryptico encryption library:

let PassPhrase = new Date + "";
let RSAKey = cryptico.generateRSAKey(PassPhrase, 1024);
let PublicKeyString = cryptico.publicKeyString(RSAKey);
let public_key = new Buffer.from(PublicKeyString, ).toString('base64');
console.log(public_key);

Activate the device

Basic Information

Path: /api/auth/activation

Method: PUT

Interface description:

This interface does not require Session authentication; the
password field uses the challenge string returned by the authentication challenge. After RSA decoding with the public key, AES encryption is performed with the decoded string and the actual password of the device. The generated string is Base64 encrypted and sent. Activate the device;
after the device is activated, the stand-alone mode is selected by default, and the server and cloud modes are not supported.

Request password generation process Javascript example, using cryptico and GibberishAES encryption library:

let CipherText = new Buffer.from(challenge, 'base64').toString();
let DecryptionResult = cryptico.decrypt(CipherText, RSAKey);
if (null !== DecryptionResult.plaintext) {
   let out = GibberishAES.enc(password, DecryptionResult.plaintext);
   let encString = new Buffer.from(out, 'utf-8').toString('base64');
   console.log(encString);
}

challenge is the field returned by the authentication-challenge interface, and RSAKey is the public key saved by the client, which is also used in the authentication-challenge interface.



Note: W5K models are temporarily not supported

Modify the user information of the specified id

Basic Information

Path: /api/auth/users/{id}

Method: PUT

Interface description:

1. AES encryption is required to modify the user password. The encryption method is as follows:
    Base64(AES(password, SessionID)), the SessionID is the session id obtained from this login, and the encryption mode is ECB/PKCS7Padding.
2. The user whose id is 1 is a fixed user. Except for the password field, other fields cannot be modified.

password_encrypt_type password encryption method field, the default is plain, using plain text password;
id_number ID number must be encrypted by aes, the key used for creation and modification uses the current session id, and the key for acquisition uses the key issued by a special interface;
Note : The keys created and modified in W5K V 1.1.9 are the keys delivered by the special interface, and have been modified after V1.2.0.

The aes encryption method is: AES (password, SessionID), the SessionID is the session id obtained from this login, and the encryption mode is ECB/PKCS7Padding;
under ws-webapi, the SessionID is the SN number as the key

The example is as follows, the password is admin123, and the SessionID is 8deebeb88f00e3f538374a8fd07ad4a9:

Base64(AES(admin123, 8deebeb88f00e3f538374a8fd07ad4a9)) = kEojZd/F6bqkHP8S3RuKoQ==

Some models (such as the W4K dynamic base library version) support the delivery of two base library images. At this time, the face_list array can deliver two image data. idx is 0 for the first base library, and idx for 1 means the dynamic base library.
Personnel photos can be up to 512KB in size

Equipment special operation

Basic Information

Path: /api/devices/operation

Method: POST

Interface description:

The interface for performing special operations on the device, such as restoring the initial value of the database, formatting the local disk, etc., is a dangerous operation and requires two-step authentication:
1. Obtain the salt value through the special operation challenge interface of the device;
2. The salt value and the operation character ( For example, "face_db_reset") performs hash ( "face_db_reset" , salt) operation, and the hash uses the SHA2-256 algorithm;
3. The calculated hash value is brought to the json string, and the corresponding operation is performed after the underlying verification is passed;

Supported operation characters:
1. face_db_reset, the configuration of personnel database, etc. is restored to the default value, without affecting the network and other parameters;
2.  id_number_aeskey, issued ID card encryption AES key, used for ID card number encryption in personnel and pass records, Must be 16/32 bytes .
3. qrcode_token, the QR code key issued by the personnel, if not issued, the default key will be used.

Encryption method of detail field:
Base64 ( AES(password, SessionID)), SessionID is the session id obtained from this login, and the encryption mode is ECB/PKCS7Padding.
Note: The detail field issued by W5K V1.1.9 is not encrypted, and V1.2.0 and later versions need to be encrypted.

After the interface is called successfully, it needs to be called after an interval of 10 minutes to prevent repeated requests.

request parameter

Headers

parameter name parameter value Required Example Remark
Content-Type application/json Yes
cookies sessionID=xxxxxx Yes xxxxxx is the sessionID returned after login authentication;

Body

nametypeRequiredDefaultsRemarkother information
typestringyesOperation type, face_db_reset-clears the database, id_number_aeskey-issues the ID encryption key, qrcode_token-issues the QR code key for personnel access

Enumeration: face_db_reset, id_number_aeskey, qrcode_token

passwordstringyesChallenge the hash value of interface and operation type, algorithm sha256
detailstringoptionalExtended information, such as ID card AES key, pass key, etc., should also be encrypted with AES.

return data

nametypeRequiredDefaultsRemarkother information

Create an access control plan

Basic Information

Path: /api/schedules/item

Method: POST

Interface description:

The access control rules are divided into two specifications according to schedule_list_type, one is crond format, the other is json format, please refer to the following rules for details:

1. CROND format

The crond rule syntax description, the time refers to the crontab format, but the time and minutes are not cyclically arranged (otherwise, like 9:20~11:20, such a simple time interval needs to set 3 rules), only supports the cycle for day, month, week and year .
A rule consists of:

time delimiter date
See below space See below

Time format description :
expressed in 24 hexadecimal;

symbol Symbol Description meaning
: colon Split, hour before, minutes after, no seconds
- minus sign Indicates the interval
, comma express parallel relationship

An example is as follows:

expression meaning
9:00-10:00 9:00 to 10:00
9:20-23:00 9:20 to 23:00\
0:00-2:00, 9:30-18:00, 23:00-23:59 In particular, if the time spans the early morning, it should be divided into multiple time periods, from 9:30 to 18:00 for the morning shift, and from 23:00 to 2:00 for the evening shift

date format description (refer to crontab):
a total of four columns, each column is separated by spaces, representing day (by month), month, day (by week), and year;

symbol Symbol Description meaning
* Asterisk all numbers in the range
/ slash how many numbers
- minus sign interval
, comma Constellation

An example is as follows:

expression meaning
* * 1-5 * Every working day (Mon – Fri)
1 * * * 1st of every month
*/2 * * * next day
1,15 9** September 1st and September 15th
15 10 * 2018 October 15, 2018
2-20 9*2018 September 2, 2018 to September 20, 2018
*/14 * * * Every other week (big and small weeks)

An example of a complete message is as follows:

{
    "cmd": "schedule_manage",
    "id": "2",
    "type": "schedules",
    "schedule_name": "test",
    "schedule_list": [
        {
            "type": "workday",
            "rule": "8:00-21:00,21:00-22:00 * * 1 *"
        },
        {
            "type": "holiday",
            "name": "holidayName",
            "rule": "8:00-21:00,21:00-22:00 9 10 * *"
        }
    ]
}
1. JSON format

The rule rule is a json string, and the workday plan is set by week. 1~7 means Monday to Sunday, and there are up to 3 time periods per day. The example is as follows:

{
    "1": "00:02-11:59,14:00-23:59",
    "2": "00:20-03:20,08:00-16:59,17:00-23:59",
    "3": "09:20-16:20",
    "4": "09:20-16:20",
    "5": "09:20-16:20",
    "6": "00:00-23:59",
    "7": "00:00-23:59"
}

The holiday plan is set by day, and each day is also three time periods. The example is as follows:
set a date period, the time period is empty, the date period is set as an impassable time range
, and the time period is not empty, the date and time segment set to passable time range

{
    "20201201": "01:00-07:59,10:00-13:59,15:00-21:59"
}

An example of a complete message is as follows:

{
    "id": "2",
    "type": "schedules",
    "schedule_name": "test",
    "schedule_list_type": "json",
    "schedule_list": [
        {
            "type": "workday",
            "rule": {
                "1": "00:02-11:59,14:00-23:59",
                "2": "00:20-03:20,08:00-16:59,17:00-23:59",
                "3": "09:20-16:20",
                "4": "09:20-16:20",
                "5": "09:20-16:20",
                "6": "00:00-23:59",
                "7": "00:00-23:59"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "holiday",
            "name": "name1",
            "rule": {
                "20201201-20201201": "01:00-07:59,10:00-13:59,15:00-21:59"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "holiday",
            "name": "name2",
            "rule": {
                "20201202-20201203": "01:00-07:59,10:00-13:59,15:00-21:59"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "holiday",
            "name": "name3",
            "rule": {
                "20201203-20201206": "01:00-07:59,10:00-13:59,15:00-21:59"
            }
        }
    ]
}

Enable log download

Basic Information

Path: /api/logs/download

Method: POST

Interface description:

Asynchronous interface. When the download is enabled successfully, it will return HTTP 202 Create. Afterwards, you need to use the Get Log Download Status API to poll the log status. When the status is ready, you can call the Download Log API to download the log file.

Note: The W5K model has no type of log download, and does not support log download for a specified period of time. When this interface is called, the interface will return the download address url, the method is Get, and then you need to use the Get log download status interface to poll the log status. When the status is ready, you can directly access the previously returned url to download the log.

Set the voice pool interface

Basic Information

Path: /api/voice/pool/item

Method: POST

Interface description:

1. Sampling rate supports 8kHz, 11.025kHz, 12kHz, 16kHz, 22.05kHz, 24kHz, 32kHz, 44.1kHz, 48kHz, 64kHz
2. Supports mono and dual channels

Only W4K models return WAV audio file error code:

error code error message Remark
-1 Invalid wav/audio data. Audio file data error
-2 Invalid wav/audio format. wrong audio file format
-3 Invalid wav/audio SR. Audio file sample rate is not 16000
-4 Invalid wav/audio NC. Audio file is not mono
-5 Invalid wav/audio BPS. Audio file sampling depth is not 16bit
